unify

public Substitution unify(Term term)
Unify this variable with an other specified term. Note, called unify does not modify the parameters of this method.

Parameters:
term - the term to unify with.
Returns:
The substitution that defines the binding constraints needed to unify this term with the other term or null if no binding constraints allows to unify the two terms.
Throws:
BindingException - if the term to unify with this variable is a variable with the same symbol as this variable and has an incompatible type, i.e., !this.getTypeSet().getSubTypes().containsAll(term.getTypeSet().getSubTypes()).
See Also:
Term.unify(Term, Substitution)

unify

public Substitution unify(Term term,
                          Substitution sigma)
Unify this variable with an other specified term by taking into account a specified set of binding constraints. Note, called unify does not modify the parameters of this method.

Parameters:
term - the term to unify with this variable.
sigma - the substitution containing the binding constraints.
Returns:
The substitution that defines the binding constraints needed to unify this term with the other term or null if no binding constraints allows to unify the two terms.
Throws:
BindingException - if the term to unify with this variable is a variable with the same symbol as this variable and has an incompatible type, i.e., !this.getTypeSet().getSubTypes().containsAll(term.getTypeSet().getSubTypes()).
